  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/3922",
  "title": "Clear single refinements",
  "body": "Something similar has been asked before, but with a different output wanted.\r\n\r\nWhat we basically need is a way to clear these 9 filters separately and **not** all at once with the current [clearRefinements](https://www.algolia.com/doc/api-reference/widgets/clear-refinements/js/).\r\n\r\n<img width=\"235\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2019-07-05 at 14 51 39\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3603346/60723612-6863d680-9f34-11e9-8239-b35438270b3d.png\">\r\n\r\nSo basically `clearRefinements` for every single \"filtergroup\". Is something like this possible with instantsearch.js?\r\n",
